comments:
EMF2SAXRenderer.doLoad catches all Exceptions even though its interface allows it to throws IOExceptions. This can create bizarre scenarios like the stack trace below, where a piece of code thinks it is handling I/O failures by catching IOException but in fact the IOException passes right by as an unchecked wrapper but shows up in the stack trace as though the exception is somehow breaking the checked exception mechanism.  Recommend the catch(Exception) at the end of this method either be removed or at least rethrow IOExceptions unwrapped while wrapping others.
